ss field experience preferred • Bachelor’s degree in Marketing, Business or a related field. • Strong understanding of branding, trade-marketing and long-term strategy development. • Demonstrated ability in preparing and negotiating business agreements. • Superior ability to communicate effectively to stakeholders to enable them to make effective decisions regarding brand licensing. • Goal oriented with experience working in cross-functional teams. • Strong organizational skills and able to devote attention to diverse products and markets • Experience and attendance at past Branding & Licensing Expos is a bonusAbout this companyHi-5 Operations Pte LtdHi-5 is a popular multiple award-winning childrens’ programme created in Australia in 1999. It reaches an estimated weekly audience of over 10 million children and is currently broadcasting in over 83 countries worldwide. Hi-5 has grown beyond the television platform to live concerts, CDs and DVDs, music, apparel and merchandising. Hi-5 has been rated one of the top 3 most successful pre-school television shows in Australia for the past 10 years and is also the No.1 programme on paid TV in Latin America. Our licensees include global entertainment and media players such as Nickelodeon, Sony Music, Channel 11 Australia, Discovery, Cartoonito and Disney Asia. We are currently looking for a dynamic individual to join our ever-expanding team in the area of branding and licensing. The candidate should be someone keen to work in Children’s entertainment and has honed skill sets to take the Hi-5 brand to new levels. Similar jobsSingaporePosted 27 days agoSingaporePosted 19 days agoSingaporePosted 19 days agoSingaporePosted 8 days agoNottingham, United…Posted 7 days agoWalsall, United KingdomPosted 28 days agoGreater Seattle AreaPosted 10 days agoFayetteville, Arkansas…Posted 27 days agoSan Francisco Bay AreaPosted 7 days agoGreater New York City…Posted 14 days agoThis is a preview of the Brand Licensing Manager job at Hi-5 Oper